  <!-- =======================================
       PROBLEMS WE SOLVE. GTM. Drew (R24): "we need to identify some
       of the problems in the space and how we solve them. That's a
       better GTM on that page."
       ======================================= -->
  <Section variant="vault" pad="default" maxWidth="wide">
    <div class="sb-problems-head">
      <div class="sb-problems-eyebrow">WHAT WE SOLVE</div>
      <h2 class="sb-problems-title">Running model-written code is the unsolved infra problem of 2026.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="sb-problems-grid">
      <div class="sb-problem">
        <div class="sb-problem-tag">UNTRUSTED CODE EXECUTION</div>
        <div class="sb-problem-pain">Models write code that needs to run somewhere. Not your laptop, too easy to wreck. Not prod, too easy to leak. Your "Docker container" doesn't isolate a confused Claude with `rm -rf` privileges or a prompt-injected agent reaching for a secret.</div>
        <div class="sb-problem-fix">→ Tangle Sandbox. VM-grade boundary, mTLS sidecar enforces egress and filesystem policy. Root inside the box, nothing crosses the wall.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sb-problem">
        <div class="sb-problem-tag">REPRODUCIBILITY ACROSS RUNS</div>
        <div class="sb-problem-pain">Agent eval needs identical environments to compare variants. Spinning up a fresh container per run takes minutes. Caching is bespoke. State drifts.</div>
        <div class="sb-problem-fix">→ Snapshot once, restore in 1.1s. Bit-identical state per variant. Hand the snapshot URL to your eval runner and parallel-fan-out across regions.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sb-problem">
        <div class="sb-problem-tag">MULTI-TENANT WORKLOADS</div>
        <div class="sb-problem-pain">One box per user, session, or task. Cross-talk between tenants is a P0. Your auth layer doesn't extend to the runtime. sidecars and IAM are bolted on.</div>
        <div class="sb-problem-fix">→ One sandbox per tenant by default. mTLS identity is the runtime identity. No shared filesystem, no shared network namespace, no leakage across tasks.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sb-problem">
        <div class="sb-problem-tag">SCALE WITHOUT WARMING</div>
        <div class="sb-problem-pain">Agent traffic is spiky. Pre-warmed pools cost money you don't bill for. Cold starts ruin the user experience. Container schedulers weren't designed for this shape.</div>
        <div class="sb-problem-fix">→ Sub-second cold-starts on demand, optional warm-pool pinning for hot paths. Pay per second of actual box-time, burst headroom 80k.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

